  THE VERY BASICS YOU NEED TO KNOW
to know present working directory type in
  pwd

for listing files we use ls and there are options for this 
it is better to use all the options like alh together 
a is for all files including hidden
l is for long format 
h is for human readable format

	ls-alh

cd to change the directory
 	 cd .. go back a step or go up a level 
	 cd ~ home directory 
	 cd / root directory 

CREATING & COPYING 
to create a file we use touch 
	touch file.type
to create a directory we usae mkdir in short form i would like to call this make directory
	mkdir name 
to create a nested directory like a directory insdie another directory 
	mkdir -p  a/b/c
to copy a file we use cp
	cp file.txt file1.txt (copies things in file.txt to file1.txt)
to copy a directory we use cp-r
 	cp -r directory directory2 (copies the directory to directory2 we use -r so that itb happens recursively)
to move a file we use mv
	mv file1 file2 


 REMOVING
 to remove we use rm 
 	rm file.txt
 	rm -r directory (removes recursively)
 	rm -rf directory (removes the diorectory forcefully dangerous to use you might delete)
 	
 CONTENTS IN A FILE 
to show contents of a file
	 cat file.type
to show the contents but singel page at a time 
	less file.type
to show the last 10 lines of a file
	tail file.type
	tail -f  file.type (follows the file as it keeps writing)
	


 	 
